  "core_payload": {
    "content_type": "markdown",
    "content": "# Workspace: The Unified Digital Command Center\n\n## 1. Definition\nWithin the N1Hub ecosystem, the **Workspace** serves as the user's primary interface and personal digital habitat. It is the command center where people interact with the sovereign graph, manage projects, and orchestrate AI capabilities without manually thinking in raw JSON or cryptographic seals.\n\n## 2. Core Components\n- **Planner**: macro-goals, decomposition, sequencing, and dependency visibility.\n- **Tracker**: execution telemetry, deadlines, drift detection, and follow-through.\n- **Dashboard**: high-level metrics, recent activity, and proactive alerts.\n- **Personal AI Assistant**: the ambient copilot for graph-grounded conversation and next actions.\n- **Chat to Capsules**: the conversational ingress path where chat becomes real capsule work.\n- **AI Wallet**: the secure provider and subscription configuration surface.\n- **AI Control Surface**: the operator-facing pane for AI status, lanes, and runtime trust.\n- **Symphony Execution Lane**: isolated repository automation and coding-agent sessions.\n- **Background Agent Runtime**: the long-lived daemon and night-shift substrate beneath autonomous capsule work.\n\n## 3. Seamless CapsuleOS Integration\nWorkspace is not separate from the graph; it is the lens through which users manipulate it. Every action can mint, modify, link, or delegate capsule work while respecting status boundaries, validation rules, and sovereignty constraints.\n\n## 4. Canonical Workspace Modules\nPlanner, Tracker, Personal AI Assistant, Chat to Capsules, AI Wallet, AI Control Surface, Symphony, and the Background Agent Runtime now form the canonical AI-capable workspace stack in N1Hub.\n"
  },
  "neuro_concentrate": {
    "summary": "Workspace is the unified digital command center and personal habitat for users inside N1Hub. It integrates planning, tracking, dashboard telemetry, assistant conversation, chat-to-capsules behavior, AI credential control, and both foreground and background execution lanes into one accountable operating surface. This capsule matters because N1Hub should not feel like disconnected tools bolted onto a graph; Workspace is where graph work, chat, delegation, repository automation, and background maintenance are experienced as one coherent habitat.",
